 <H1>An Object-Oriented World</H1> 
 <P><H2>An Object-Oriented World</H2>
</P>
<P><UL><LI>Example: Watching TV<UL><LI>From �Learn Java Now�, Stephen R. Davis, Microsoft Press</UL><LI>A TV is a physical object<UL><LI>A TV is a well-defined concept with well-defined boundaries<LI>The concept of TV is universally understood</UL><LI>A TV remote control provides user interface<UL><LI>No other interface is needed<LI>No additional knowledge of TV internals is needed</UL><LI>A TV �works� right out of the box<UL><LI>Robust, fully operational, not expected to fail<LI>Its relations/ attachments to the world are fully documented</UL></UL></P>
